claim.claim-text:
A construction machine comprising:
an automotive vehicle body (3);
a working mechanism (4) provided on the front part side of said vehicle body (3);
a counterweight (7) removably provided on the rear part side of said vehicle body (3) in order to hold weight balance with said working mechanism (4);
an engine (9) mounted on said vehicle body (3) located on the front side of said counterweight (7); and
an exhaust gas post-treatment device (21) provided in the middle of an exhaust gas passage of said engine (9) and configured to apply purification treatment to an exhaust gas by using a single treatment device or by connecting a plurality of treatment devices (22, 23, 41), characterized in that:
at least one treatment device (23, 41) constituting said exhaust gas post-treatment device (21) is configured to be fixed to said counterweight (7) when said counterweight (7) is mounted on said vehicle body (3); and
a treatment device support member (26, 31, 42, 26') for supporting said at least one treatment device (23, 41) is provided on one member of said engine (9) and said vehicle body (3) when said counterweight (7) is removed from said vehicle body (3).

The construction machine according to claim 2, wherein between said one member of said engine (9) and said vehicle body (3) and said vehicle-body side fixing portion (31A) of said treatment device support member (31), a spacer (33) that removably mounted between the both is provided;

when said counterweight (7) is removed from said vehicle body (3), said vehicle-body side fixing portion (31A) of said treatment device support member (31) is mounted on said one member through said spacer (33), and said at least one treatment device (23) is mounted on said weight-side fixing portion (31B) of said treatment device support member (31); and

when said counterweight (7) is mounted on said vehicle body (3), a gap (32) is formed between said vehicle-body side fixing portion (31A) of said treatment device support member (31) and said one member by removing said spacer (33), and said weight-side fixing portion (31B) of said treatment device support member (31) is mounted on said counterweight (7) together with said at least one treatment device (23).

The construction machine according to claim 1, wherein on said at least one treatment device (41), a first mounting leg portion (41D) mounted on said counterweight (7) when said counterweight (7) is mounted on said vehicle body (3) and a second mounting leg portion (41E) arranged at a position different from that of said first mounting leg portion (41D) are provided;

said treatment device support member (42) has a support arm portion (42A) arranged by extending in the front-rear direction between said engine (9) and said counterweight (7), said vehicle-body side fixing portion (42B) provided on the front side of said support arm portion (42A) and fixed to said one member (9) of said engine (9) and said vehicle body (3), and a weight-side fixing portion (42C) provided on the rear side of said support arm portion (42A) and fixed to said second mounting leg portion (41E) of said at least one treatment device (41); and

when said counterweight (7) is to be removed from said vehicle body (3), said first mounting leg portion (41D) of said at least one treatment device (41) is removed from said counterweight (7), and said second mounting leg portion (41E) is mounted on said weight-side fixing portion (42C) of said treatment device support member (42).
